b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Character.ai is best suited for roleplay, entertainment, creative writing, character interaction, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Cohere, meanwhile, shines for enterprise RAG, developers, search applications, business AI, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Character.ai describes itself as \"Chat with AI versions of any character, real or fictional.\" Cohere, established in 2019, positions itself as \"Enterprise AI platform focused on retrieval-augmented generation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Cohere** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (5 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Character.ai is a poor choice — far from it. Character.ai excels in its own right, particularly for roleplay and entertainment.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent retrieval-augmented generation, go with Cohere. If massive library of community-created characters matters more to you, Character.ai is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
